review_blob: Bottle. Belgian stouts appear to be sweeter than the British stouts. Just a bit too sweet for my taste. Im not sure of the attraction of this one.
Bottle. Doesnt taste the strength. Some usual stout features, but quite sweet. I was pleased to try this, but I wasnt impressed.

Bottle. This is a bit of fun. Not a beer to take seriously. Its a sort of comic beer. A spoonful of sugar helps the medicine go down. Its not great, its not clever, but - apart from raging toothache from the sugar rot, this is an enjoyable ten minutes.
Bottle. Mine was not live. I think the bottles are pasteurised despite what it says on the label. Even so, this is one of the better bottled stouts Ive sampled this winter.
Bottle. A good tasty stout. Plenty of interest. Good tasty flavours in harmony. Comforting yet exciting mouthfeel. Jolly good.

Bottle. After trying a number of stouts and porters recently I found this to be the least interesting. Nicely drinakble. Soft. Sort of like a Big Mac. Easy drinking and comforting. A deceptive beer. But even with the lack of character, and some plastic flavour, it is a beer that I wouldnt say no to. I understand this was the first of the modern Oatmeal Stouts.
Bottle. Chocolate aroma with some coffee flavours. The usual flavours youd get in a stout. But not exciting.
Cask conditioned. This won at the Camra Winter Festival last year, and fully deserved. This is full of chcolate and coffee  flavours all wrapped up in a sweet yet sour blanket.
From the bottle. This is a very dark and sturdy winter ale. Soft, smooth and sweet, yet with enough dark bitter chocolate to give interesting contrasts.
Bottle from Sainsburys. Clean enough, with a touch of noble sweetness and some fragrant lemony hops. An advance on a German wine. I really liked this and will no doubt get some more.
A pint of espresso please. Not really! The darkness is the big thing here. And the creamy head. Flavours have softened over time.
Supermarket bottle. Very strong tasting with a big head and some off flavours like stale spices in an Indian shop.
Hand pulled from the cask. Stronger than the regular brewers gold this goes a notch higher in every respect and is very exciting.
From the cask. Fruity flavours both sweet and sharp. Very clean and refreshing.
Famous dark mild. Black colour, like the cat. Chocolate and Christmas cake flavours. Soft but tasty palate. Excellent.
Supermarket bottle. A summer drink that is fairly crisp and refreshing but is not top drawer.
A standard lager with not much taste. Thin looking with an off flavour in the aroma. Waste of time.
Another famous beer. Bottle bought at Pitfield - a great beer shop in London. Packed with flavours that come wave after wave. Great palate. A classic, deserving of the reputation.
Prize winning and famous beer. Good settled flavours and decent palate. Quality all the way through.
This is more metallic and much thinner than I remember it being. The flavours are not that pronounced, nor that great. The famous nutty quality just  gives a wierd off flavour.
Light and fragrant. An easy drinking golden bitter with clean flavours from an average brewery.
Belgian strong beer. Great name. Great beer. Sweet and a bit flowery. Assorted flavours that go together well.

Beautifully balanced beer. Good strength flavour, aroma, hops, crispness and sweetness.
Great on draft on a hot summer evening. Wonderful!
Nice beer but not much of a stout. A shame because this brewery produces some excellent beers. The stout is lacking in texture, smoothness and body.
Nectar! I dont understand the skunk references in some of the reviews. This is a great malty, sweet, heavy and hoppy beer. Excellent.

Do folks still drink this?
Gassy, tasteless - a classic mass produced lager.
Dull, dull, dull, dull, DULL! A triumph of marketing not of brewing!
A great standby - always worth having in the fridge. There are better lagers but there are far worse - Jupiler for a start!
A great British bitter - smooth, malty, hoppy. What more could you want out of a pint?
Dont know how they managed it but they seem to have achieved an unpleasant bitterness with no hop flavour or aroma. Will avoid the stuff in the future.
